textBeforeTable: TOP PUBLISHERS Here's the charts: Diamond released their top comics charts for April 2014 last week, and The Outhouse got EXCLUSIVE comments from Hitler on the numbers, which show a big gain for Marvel thanks to the success of Amazing Spider-Man #1. Though DC's Batman titles, particularly Batman Eternal, took six of the top ten, Marvel still took nearly 15% more of unit and market share, while Image Comics continues to hold strong at around 10% with a great showing on the graphic novels chart.
